gmx:name.gco:CharacterString: Feature catalog for Cities and Towns of the United States, 2014

gmx:scope.gco:CharacterString: Cities and towns; Administrative and political divisions; Population

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: A city or town in the United States, Puerto Rico, or the U.S. Virgin Islands. A city or town is a place with a recorded population, usually with at least one central area that provides commercial activities. Cities are generally larger than towns; no distinction is made between cities and towns in this map layer.
Internal feature number.

gfc:definition.gco:CharacterString: Place or area with clustered or scattered buildings and a permanent human population (city, settlement, town, village.) A populated place is usually not incorporated and by definition has no legal boundaries. However, a populated place may have a corresponding "civil" record, the legal boundaries of which may or may not coincide with the perceived populated place. Distinct from Census and Civil classes.
